text: Don't Give Up!  Knock on doors.  Phonebank.  Text Bank.  Talk to the people you're standing in line with at the grocery store.  Talk to people at the bus stop.  Spread the word that Bernie is not out of the race yet!Y’all with your negativity. Bernie is within 6% of Biden with delegates. There are almost 2500 delegates left. And I’ve listed the states and how many delegates are remaining.  Out of the states remaining, Bernie won a lot of those in 2016. I’ve also included a map of the 2016 results. There are a few differences in the map from 2016 with the 2020 map, one big difference is Bernie didn’t win California in 2016. Plus, he was further behind after Super Tuesday in 2016. It was not just 6% then. I’ve also included a picture of this. In addition, I’ve included a map of where we currently stand after Super Tuesday excluding Maine which was decided for Biden today.  If we can get some of the same states we got in 2016 (Michigan, Indiana) it will help. If we could gain Ohio, Pennsylvania, and New York, it would help.  Yes, Texas hurt, Maine hurt, Massachusetts hurts...but we still get a decent amount of delegates in those states.  Stay positive! Keep donating! Keep campaigning! Keep calling!!!! And, damnit, show up to vote!!! Going to rallies is not enough. Do not become complacent.  Bernie said he’d announce his VP after Super Tuesday, let’s hope that happens and let’s hope he hits it out of the park. Mississippi, the political establishment has left you behind. Many of us feel the establishment candidates no longer represent us, the people of Mississippi.  The DNC has all but ended funding in the South, essentially announcing to America that we're beyond saving. Progressives Disagree, and we need your help. I am Jensen Bohren, a Berniecrat running for US Senate to represent OUR forgotten state of Mississippi. I relate to Mississippian's struggles, needs, and desires because I am one of you. But-- I cannot do this alone. In Mississippi, it costs nearly $3000 to purchase the voting records, a necessary step in reaching out to voters. We need two hundred $15 donations as soon as possible. As a Progressive candidate, I pledge to share the voting records with any other progressive candidates who need this information to campaign. To sweeten the deal, for every $50 or larger in-state donation will get a campaign exclusive edition of "Politics! The Card Game." Bernie Sanders believes in our ability to organize at the local level, and I do, too.

text: Though the news cycle has forgotten the Canton Raids, the people affected are still having difficulty.  If you can assist, please do.MRC COMMUNITY MEMBERS-- Our migrant brothers and sisters impacted by the ICE raids still need our help!  Dozens of workers, who were the breadwinners for their families, either remain detained awaiting bond hearings, or have been released on bond and are awaiting hearings in immigration court and are unable to find work. Resources donated 3 months ago are being depleted, but the work of supporting these families is ongoing and will continue for the months ahead. As part of the MS Immigration Coalition, a collective of organizations committed to responding to the long-term legal and humanitarian crises resulting from the raids, we are collecting donations which will be used to cover expenses related to food, transport, healthcare expenses, rent and utility assistance and other material support for impacted workers and their families. 100% of donations will go directly to this grassroots humanitarian support. Please give what you can. Donate via PayPal @ PayPal.Me/msrising
